# Secure Force — SAST and Deploy Gate

When running a security scan, before deploy, or when editing these files (auth, config, env, main app):

1. **Run SAST:** Execute Semgrep so automated checks run first.
   ```bash
   semgrep scan --config auto
   ```
   Fix or document any findings before shipping.

2. **Load security context:** Read [SECURE-FORCE.md](SECURE-FORCE.md). Use the threat model and OWASP-oriented checklist. Manually review every user-input path and auth route; SAST does not catch semantic issues.

3. **Review before deploy:** Do not ship on "it runs." Review AI-generated (or any) auth logic, input validation, and data connections. Ensure no hardcoded credentials and no internal errors exposed to the client.

4. **Infra (if applicable):** If the project has Docker, Terraform, K8s, or cloud configs, run an infrastructure/config scanner and set resource limits.

This rule ensures the AI (and you) have the right context when touching sensitive code and before release.
